h Ga2O3-diamond interfaces are about 20% smaller\nthan that of the clean interface, indicating interface chemistry affects\ninterfacial thermal transport. Overall, this study shows that a high TBC can be\nobtained from strong interfacial bonds across Ga2O3-diamond interfaces,\nproviding a promising route to improving the heat dissipation from Ga2O3\ndevices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Aug 2019 05:05:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-26"}
